task.summary: * use of '_' as an identifier might not be supported in releases after Java SE 8 * varargs should be a single Object xor Object[] * junit.framework.Assert is deprecated, also the entire Test could be deleted as it’s dead code
* use generic-enabled methods like Collections.emptyList/Set/Map() instead of Collections.EMPTY_LIST * use singleton lists for better performance where possible

* revert being more specific about varargs as it causes a runtime issue in this particular implementation
* replace manual array copy * StringBuilder should use append and not concatenate inbetween * String.format should not be used where it is not required
* improve performance in tests (for benchmarks?) by using singleton lists * Strings do not need a constructor except for JVM-internal tests regarding “reference vs value” tests
#360 make tests fail because of unfillfilled assertions and not because of unexpected behavior; harden CompilationResult class

* introduce RoundingMode to prevent ArithmeticError exceptions (because of non-deterministic decimal expansion) * fix erroneous overriding (potential runtime issues) of equals (if an obj is an instance of something, it cannot be null) * fix clone signature * make pseudo-constants actual constants * private methods cannot be overriden, hence making them final is just noisy
#367 fix Solidity compilation issue on Macs

Code cleanup, reduction of potentially undefined behavior, and a performance improvement
* introduce RoundingMode to prevent ArithmeticError exceptions (because of non-deterministic decimal expansion) * fix erroneous overriding (potential runtime issues) of equals (if an obj is an instance of something, it cannot be null) * fix clone signature * make pseudo-constants actual constants * replace manual array copy (performance issue)
Further code cleanup * fix potential issue: mixed up “ip” w/ “id”? * private methods cannot be overridden, hence making them final is just noisy
